            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EHistory%20is%20replete%20with%20stories%20of%20the%20rise%20and%20fall%20of%20persecutors%20of%20the%20Church%2C%20but%20the%20worst%20persecutor%20of%20all%20time%20could%20arrive%20in%20our%20generation.%20We%20may%20or%20may%20not%20be%20around%20when%20the%20actual%20Antichrist%20arrives%20on%20the%20scene%2C%20but%20the%20%22spirit%20of%20the%20Antichrist%22%20(1%20John%204%3A3)%20has%20been%20working%20for%20thousands%20of%20years.%20It%20is%20a%20deceptive%20spirit%2C%20seeking%20to%20deny%20that%20Jesus%20is%20the%20Christ%20and%20thus%20denying%20the%20Father%20and%20the%20Son%20(2%3A22).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDaniel%20received%20the%20greatest%20Old%20Testament%20revelation%20of%20the%20Antichrist.%20He%20foresaw%20the%20covenant%20the%20Antichrist%20will%20make%20with%20the%20Jewish%20people%20in%20the%20seven%20years%20known%20as%20the%20Tribulation.%20The%20Antichrist%20will%20suddenly%20turn%20on%20the%20Jewish%20nation%20and%20%22set%20up%20a%20sacrilegious%20object%20that%20causes%20desecration%22%20(Daniel%209%3A27).%20It%20will%20be%20an%20image%20of%20the%20Antichrist%20himself%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20Jews'%20rebuilt%20temple.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWe%20are%20not%20deceived%2C%20however%2C%20because%20we%20have%20the%20truth%20of%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20living%20in%20us%20(1%20John%202%3A20).%20Let%20us%20fear%20neither%20the%20literal%20Antichrist%20nor%20the%20spirit%20of%20Antichrist.%20The%20greater%20One%20is%20living%20inside%20us!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
